- Connect MikroTik to Interface 10/100 in OLT
- Set IP 136.1.1.200/24 in Mikrotik then ping to 136.1.1.100 (OLT)
- Telnet to 136.1.1.100 (via MikroTik di Tools > Telnet)


Enable plug-and-play of the OLT boards and add the chassis type
##################################################################
conf t
set-pnp enable
add-rack rackno 1 racktype C320Rack
add-shelf rackno 1 shelfno 1 shelftype C320_SHELF
add-card rackno 1 shelfno 1 slotno 2 GTGH (i used GTGH)
add-card slotno 3 PRAM (if used PRAM)
add-subcard rackno 1 shelfno 1 slotno 4 subcardno 1 UCDC/3
##################################################################

Configure a new management IP address on the (out-of-band) mng1 interface:
##################################################################
conf t
interface mng1
ip address 10.19.4.2 255.255.255.252
exit
line telnet idle-timeout 15 (15 menit default)
end
##################################################################

Configure IP and VLAN via Uplink Port (i used gei_1/4/3)
##################################################################
conf t
vlan 2543 (VLAN ID for Management)    #Please config this VLAN in Router, and Switch if OLT not direcly connected to Router
exit
interface vlan2543
ip address 10.25.43.3 255.255.255.0   #10.25.43.1 as Gateway in Router
exit
ip route 0.0.0.0 0.0.0.0 10.25.43.3   #uplink via VLAN 2543
line telnet idle-timeout 15           #15 menit default
ip route 0.0.0.0 0.0.0.0 136.1.1.1    #ke IP MGNT
end
write
##################################################################
